  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n forge script script/DeployElliptic.s.sol:MyScript --rpc-url https://ethereum-sepolia.blockpi.network/v1/rpc/public --private-key <> --etherscan-api-key <> --verify \n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen aliases are used with remappings, the --verify flag fails, with a path error. While the compilation of sources is fine, the verify script is not able to interpret correctly the path to src/ if it is not in the main directory.\r\n\r\nIn this case remappings is external to the directory where 'forge init' was made, to keep sources separated from the workplace.\r\ntoml line:\r\nremappings = [\"@solidity/=../../../solidity/src\",\"@external/=../../../solidity/external/\"]\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/103030189/2e090931-219f-4e91-a6a2-088ad418aef0)\r\n\r\n",
